Mining Review has launched its weekly podcast series, Deep Insights. Listen each week as industry experts discuss pertinent matters relating to the African mining industry. This week, Deep Insights speaks to Dr Thuthule Balfour, head of health at Minerals Council South Africa about ramping up operations amid the COVID-19 pandemic. Was the national lockdown necessary? What can mining companies do to safeguard their workers? How do they protect mining communities and what can in expect in a post COVID-19 mine? The podcast is available online and also on all popular platforms for download. Simply subscribe here to access Deep Insights. Read more about COVID-19